arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a veterinary clinic management Blazor Web App. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-459d36428f794e608255d4e72239eb3e/VetClinic` using `dotnet new blazor -int Server -ai -au Individual --no-https`. It targets net11.0 and uses SQLite + EF Core + ASP.NET Core Identity.

The app uses global Interactive Server rendering (via `PageRenderMode` in `App.razor`). All pages are interactive by default. Identity/Account pages are static SSR and should NOT be modified.

## What to implement

### 1. Data Models (create `Data/Models.cs`)

```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data;

public class Pet
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Species { get; set; } = "";  // Dog, Cat, Bird, etc.
    public string Breed { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public string OwnerName { get; set; } = "";
    public string OwnerPhone { get; set; } = "";
    public string OwnerEmail { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime RegisteredDate { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public List<MedicalRecord> MedicalRecords { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Invoice> Invoices { get; set; } = new();
}

public class MedicalRecord
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime Date { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Diagnosis { get; set; } = "";
    public string Treatment { get; set; } = "";
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
    public string VetName { get; set; } = "";
}

public class Appointment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime ScheduledDate { get; set; }
    public TimeSpan Duration { get; set; } = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30);
    public string Reason { get; set; } = "";
    public string VetName { get; set; } = "";
    public AppointmentStatus Status { get; set; } = AppointmentStatus.Scheduled;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
}

public enum AppointmentStatus
{
    Scheduled,
    Completed,
    Cancelled,
    NoShow
}

public class Invoice
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime IssuedDate { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public DateTime? PaidDate { get; set; }
    public List<InvoiceItem> Items { get; set; } = new();
    public decimal TotalAmount => Items.Sum(i => i.Amount);
    public InvoiceStatus Status { get; set; } = InvoiceStatus.Unpaid;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
}

public enum InvoiceStatus
{
    Unpaid,
    Paid,
    Overdue,
    Cancelled
}

public class InvoiceItem
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
}
```

### 2. Update ApplicationDbContext (`Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`)

Add DbSets for all entities and configure relationships in `OnModelCreating`.

### 3. Create a ClinicService (`Data/ClinicService.cs`)

Create a scoped service that wraps all data access operations:
- Pets: GetAll, GetById, Create, Update, Delete
- MedicalRecords: GetByPetId, Create
- Appointments: GetAll, GetByDate, GetByPetId, Create, Update, Cancel, GetAvailableSlots(date)
- Invoices: GetAll, GetByPetId, Create, AddItem, MarkPaid

For `GetAvailableSlots`, assume the clinic operates 9:00-17:00 with 30-minute slots. Return slots that don't conflict with existing scheduled appointments.

### 4. Register service and apply migrations in Program.cs

After `builder.Services.AddSingleton<IEmailSender<ApplicationUser>, IdentityNoOpEmailSender>();`, add:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<ClinicService>();
```

Before `app.Run();`, add:
```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.Migrate();
}
```

Also disable the `RequireConfirmedAccount` requirement (set it to `false`) so staff can register and log in without email confirmation.

### 5. Create Pages

Remove the template pages `Components/Pages/Home.razor`, `Components/Pages/Counter.razor`, `Components/Pages/Weather.razor` and `Components/Pages/Error.razor` (keep Error.razor actually).

Create these pages (all under `Components/Pages/`):

#### `Dashboard.razor` (@page "/")
Simple dashboard showing:
- Total patients count
- Today's appointments count  
- Unpaid invoices count
- Quick links to main sections

#### `Patients/PatientList.razor` (@page "/patients")
- Table of all patients with search/filter
- "Register New Pet" button that opens an inline form
- Click a patient row to navigate to detail

#### `Patients/PatientDetail.razor` (@page "/patients/{Id:int}")
- Pet info (editable inline)
- Medical history tab (list + "Add Record" form)
- Appointments tab
- Invoices tab

#### `Appointments/AppointmentCalendar.razor` (@page "/appointments")
- Date picker to select a day
- Shows time slots for the selected day (9:00-17:00, 30-min slots)
- Available slots are green/clickable, booked slots show the appointment info
- Click available slot to open "New Appointment" form (select patient, reason, vet)
- Existing appointments can be rescheduled (change date/time) or cancelled

#### `Billing/InvoiceList.razor` (@page "/billing")
- Table of all invoices with status filter (All, Unpaid, Paid, Overdue)
- "New Invoice" button
- Click to view/edit invoice

#### `Billing/InvoiceDetail.razor` (@page "/billing/{Id:int}")
- Invoice header (patient, date, status)
- Line items (add/remove)
- "Mark as Paid" button
- Total calculation

### 6. Update NavMenu (`Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor`)

Replace the template nav items with:
- Dashboard (/)
- Patients (/patients)
- Appointments (/appointments)
- Billing (/billing)

Keep the existing auth-related nav items (login status, etc).

### 7. Add `[Authorize]` to all pages

Every page (Dashboard, PatientList, PatientDetail, AppointmentCalendar, InvoiceList, InvoiceDetail) must have `@attribute [Authorize]` so staff must log in.

### 8. Create EF Core migration

After all model changes, run:
```bash
cd /tmp/sv-459d36428f794e608255d4e72239eb3e/VetClinic && dotnet ef migrations add InitialClinic
```

### 9. Build verification

Run `dotnet build` to ensure everything compiles.

## Important notes:
- Do NOT modify anything under `Components/Account/` — those are Identity pages and must stay as-is.
- Do NOT add `@rendermode` to pages — global interactivity is already configured.
- Use `@inject ClinicService ClinicService` for data access in components.
- Use proper Blazor patterns: `OnInitializedAsync`, `EditForm` with model binding, etc.
- For real-time feel on the appointment calendar, after any change refresh the available slots.
- All forms should use `EditForm` with a model class and basic validation.
- Use Bootstrap 5 classes for styling (already included in the template).

